039/**
040 * A subclass of {@link RestRequest} with additional features for mocked testing.
041 *
042 * <p>
043 * Instances of this class are instantiated through methods on {@link MockRestClient} such as {@link MockRestClient#post(Object,Object)}
044 *
045 * <h5 class='section'>Notes:</h5><ul>
046 *    <li class='warn'>This class is not thread safe.
047 * </ul>
048 *
049 * <h5 class='section'>See Also:</h5><ul>
050 *    <li class='link'><a class="doclink" href="https://juneau.apache.org/docs/topics/JuneauRestMockBasics">juneau-rest-mock Basics</a>
051 * </ul>
052 */
053@FluentSetters(ignore="uriScheme")
054public class MockRestRequest extends org.apache.juneau.rest.client.RestRequest {
055
056   //------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
057   // Servlet request override values.
058   //------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
059   private Map<String,Object> attributeMap = map();
060   private Map<String,RequestDispatcher> requestDispatcherMap = map();
061   private String characterEncoding, protocol, scheme, serverName, remoteAddr, remoteHost, localName, localAddr,
062      pathInfo, pathTranslated, contextPath, queryString, remoteUser, requestedSessionId, requestURI, servletPath, authType;
063   private Integer serverPort, remotePort, localPort;
064   private Locale locale;
065   private ServletContext servletContext;
066   private DispatcherType dispatcherType;
067   private Cookie[] cookies;
068   private Principal userPrincipal;
069   private HttpSession httpSession;
070   private String[] roles;
071
072   /**
073    * Constructs a REST call with the specified method name.
074    *
075    * @param client The client that created this request.
076    * @param uri The target URI.
077    * @param method The HTTP method name (uppercase).
078    * @param hasBody Whether this method has a body.
079    * @throws RestCallException If an exception or non-200 response code occurred during the connection attempt.
080    */
081   protected MockRestRequest(RestClient client, URI uri, String method, boolean hasBody) throws RestCallException {
082      super(client, uri, method, hasBody);
083   }
084
085   //------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
086   // MockServletRequest passthrough methods.
087   //------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
088
089   /**
090    * Adds an attribute to the underlying {@link HttpServletRequest} object.
091    *
092    * <p>
093    * This value gets copied to the servlet request after the call to {@link HttpClientConnection#sendRequestHeader(HttpRequest)}
094    * and right before {@link HttpClientConnection#sendRequestEntity(HttpEntityEnclosingRequest)}.
095    *
096    * @param name The servlet request attribute name.
097    * @param value The servlet request attribute value.
098    * @return This object.
099    */
100   public MockRestRequest attribute(String name, Object value) {
101      this.attributeMap.put(name, value);
102      return this;
103   }
104
105   /**
106    * Replaces the attributes on the underlying {@link HttpServletRequest} object.
107    *
108    * <p>
109    * This value gets copied to the servlet request after the call to {@link HttpClientConnection#sendRequestHeader(HttpRequest)}
110    * and right before {@link HttpClientConnection#sendRequestEntity(HttpEntityEnclosingRequest)}.
111    *
112    * @param value The new servlet attribute values.
113    * @return This object.
114    */
115   public MockRestRequest attributes(Map<String,Object> value) {
116      this.attributeMap.clear();
117      this.attributeMap.putAll(value);
118      return this;
119   }
120
121   /**
122    * Returns the attributes to add to the underlying {@link HttpServletRequest} object.
123    *
124    * @return The attributes to add to the underlying {@link HttpServletRequest} object.
125    */
126   public Map<String,Object> getAttributeMap() {
127      return attributeMap;
128   }
